supportive_care:
- item: Avoid triggers
  details: Stop any new suspected trigger (food/supplement/med) if safe to do so;
    avoid hot showers which can worsen itching.
- item: Skin care
  details: Cool compresses; fragrance-free moisturizer; avoid scratching.
followup_and_safety:
- item: Re-evaluation
  details: If hives persist >24–48h, recur frequently, or you need frequent medication
    dosing—seek in-person evaluation.
- item: Urgent/ED now
  details: Any trouble breathing, throat tightness, swelling of lips/tongue/face,
    fainting, severe dizziness, or widespread blistering rash—call 911/go to ED.
